snippet.textDisplay: This sounds to me like a mixture of Chasing Ghosts, Let The Ocean Take Me and Misery. I loved CG, LTOTM and TCBH, and Misery had a few great songs that I liked. I first discovered TAA in 2015 before I moved out of my hometown. At the time I was homeless and had a mental breakdown. Everyday I was really depressed and wished I never woke up. Their music helped to save my life. It inspired me to seek help and shortly after starting therapy I moved to the city I'm currently in and I'm doing much better. I still go to therapy but I'm able to manage my life easier. This band will always have a special place in my life... 😍😍😍😍
